OL,3,CKiller driver's 'woefully inadequate'
OL,4,Csentence to be reviewed
OL,6,FIn a letter to Caroline Johnson, the
OL,7,FMP for Sleaford and North Hykeham, who
OL,8,Fhas supported calls for the sentence
OL,9,Fto be re-examined, Solicitor General
OL,10,FEllie Reeves said: "My office has
OL,11,Freceived numerous requests to review
OL,12,Fthis sentence.
OL,14,F"I share your concerns about the
OL,15,Fsentence imposed, which I have now
OL,16,Freviewed. I can only properly refer a
OL,17,Fcase to the Court of Appeal if I
OL,18,Fconsider that the sentence appears not
OL,19,Fjust lenient, but unduly lenient... it
OL,20,Fappears to me that this test has been
OL,21,Fmet."
